comments.content: Maybe something out of the Vienna Secession? Perhaps the specimen off which [Stoclet](http://web.archive.org/web/20071009211428/http:/www.fonts.com/findfonts/detail.htm?pid=437684&grab_id=0&page_id=21719&query=stoclet%20family&SCOPE=Fonts) was based might yield something.
I think it’s something Dutch from the beginning of the century.
i don’t know, but I like it too! I wonder what the lower case would look like? Probably doesn’t have one. The old school was sensible like that.
nobody has any clue? I think it’s from around 1905.
